N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 15 ยง 70.2 - Definition

State Regulations

Hydrocarbon gas means a combustible organic gas containing
only carbon and hydrogen. Hyrdrocarbon gas includes propane, compressed natural
gas, liquified petroleum gas, methane or any chemically similar gas, but does
not include gasoline or diesel fuel. Notes
